# PawPal+ Rules

All core rules live in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). This file mirrors them for Cursor.

## Stack

Python 3.11+, Streamlit, pytest. No TypeScript, no Node.

## Architecture

- `pawpal_system.py` — all business logic (6 dataclasses: Task, Pet, ScheduledSlot, Schedule, Scheduler, Owner)
- `app.py` — Streamlit UI only
- New features → new module files (e.g., `ai_scheduler.py`)
- Do not add classes to `pawpal_system.py` unless extending a core model

## Coding Rules

- Type hints on all params and return types
- Docstring on every public method and class
- SOLID strictly (SRP, OCP, LSP, ISP, DIP)
- DRY — extract repeated logic to shared methods
- No inline comments

## Testing Rules

- TDD: write failing test first, then implement
- No mocks of `pawpal_system.py` — use real objects
- Happy path + edge cases (zero/empty/boundary) for every feature
- UI logic is also tested
- pytest only; files in `tests/`

## Naming

- `snake_case` everywhere
- UUID identity fields use `id` suffix
- Match existing style in `pawpal_system.py`

## Commit Rules

- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `test:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`
- One concern per commit
- Reference task/feature in commit body

## Hard Limits (ask user before doing)

- Adding packages to `requirements.txt`
- Adding file I/O / database / persistence
- Changing fields on Task, Pet, Owner, Schedule, ScheduledSlot
- Refactoring working code outside current task

## Self-Maintenance

If a rule becomes outdated, update this file **and** `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.
